Alexander Isak Returns To Liverpool Training Before FA Cup Quarter-Final

Liverpool FC • April 2, 2026

Alexander Isak is back in Liverpool team training after spending roughly four months out with a fractured leg and ankle injury, giving the squad a timely boost heading into the FA Cup quarter-final against Manchester City.

The striker had been sidelined since December, when he suffered the injury during Liverpool's match against Tottenham. His return to full team work was confirmed on Thursday, April 2, 2026.

Manager Arne Slot now has Isak back on the grass with the squad, although the club will still assess his condition before deciding whether he can be involved this weekend.

Even if Liverpool ease him back carefully, the update is a major lift for the run-in as the team enters the final stretch of the season and pushes on multiple fronts.
